race.comment: SMART AND MIGHTY (3) resumes. Much better effort at his second race start, when fourth over 1200m at Pakenham Synthetic. Fitted with two good jump out wins and has a host of gear changes for this. Gets his chance from the draw. HAZ STYLES (2) was in the money at Wagga when resuming two runs back then could only manage fourth here over 900m two weeks ago. Peaking now and shapes as a big threat. LORD LIMERICK (9) is on debut for the Donna Scott stable. Three-year-old gelding by All Too Hard from Lady Von Costa. Raced quite greenly but ultimately proved too good in a Seymour jump-out in readiness and gets McDougall to pilot. Keep an eye on betting moves. STEP QUICK (4) in need of the run on resumption when sixth at Canberra. Showed ability on the provincial tracks last time in. Can improve quickly. BRON (6) resumes after struggling on the heavy surface when ninth over 900m at this track on August 19. Winner of her most recent jump out at Wangaratta. Keeping safe.
